---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Running In Production | serial-sync"
  description="How to operate serial-sync safely in production."
  currentPath="/production/"
>
  <div class="page">
    <section class="section">
      <p class="eyebrow">Production</p>
      <h1>Operate it like a containerized sync system, not a browser script.</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        The runtime model is simple: Docker is the intended execution environment, Patreon sessions
        are reused when possible, and live HTTP stays behind the shared request-budget path.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>What steady state looks like</h2>
      <div class="grid-3">
        <article class="card">
          <p class="card__label">State</p>
          <h3>SQLite tracks runs</h3>
          <p>One row per run. Durable catalog state stays in SQLite; bulky payloads stay on disk.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <p class="card__label">Logs</p>
          <h3>Run logs land in state</h3>
          <p>Each run writes human-readable and JSONL logs under the configured log root.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <p class="card__label">Recovery</p>
          <h3>Support bundles are first-class</h3>
          <p>Use debug bundles to capture run context, logs, and payload references when something shifts.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Production loop</h2>
      <ol class="steps">
        <li>Keep the config declarative and source-driven.</li>
        <li>Reuse the saved Patreon session instead of bootstrapping every cycle.</li>
        <li>Keep live HTTP behind the request-budget and cooldown path.</li>
        <li>Publish only after the sync plan and materialized output look right.</li>
        <li>Inspect failures with `debug run`, `debug events`, and `debug bundle`.</li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Operator commands</h2>
      <div class="command-block">
        <pre><code>serial-sync run --dry-run --source example-creator
serial-sync run --source example-creator --target local-files
serial-sync debug runs
serial-sync debug run &lt;run-id&gt;
serial-sync debug events &lt;run-id&gt; --component publish
serial-sync debug bundle &lt;run-id&gt;</code></pre>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Production guardrails</h2>
      <div class="grid-2">
        <article class="callout">
          <h3>Do</h3>
          <p>Use Docker, saved sessions, dry-runs, and support bundles as the normal operator loop.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="callout">
          <h3>Don’t</h3>
          <p>Bypass the request budget, reintroduce ad hoc browser dependence, or treat browser auth as steady state.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>When auth breaks</h2>
      <p>
        If Patreon forces reauth, complete the challenge in the dedicated Chromium profile next to
        the session file or import a fresh session bundle. If the challenge is a TOTP step, configure
        `totp_secret_env` and retry.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
